children.text: There has not been adequate clearance of at least 150mm provided under the decking sub-floor frame to the ground, resulting in a damp environment, which according to the BCA, encourages timber rot, fungus growth and the potential for termite activity.
Part 3.4.1 of the National Construction Code’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) states that
‘Part 3.4.1 applies to the subfloor space of all suspended floors of a building or deck, including but not limited to, timber and steel-framed subfloors and suspended concrete slabs’
‘sub-floor spaces must have clearance between the ground surface and the underside of the lowest horizontal member in the subfloor in accordance with Table 3.4.1.1’.
The builder will need to extend the ground clearances to a minimum of 150mm under the decking to comply with part 3.4.1.2 of the BCA.
